The paper deals with the explanation of CNN decisions, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of an adversary to manipulate the model also falls under the category of adversarial attacks, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the security implications of manipulated explanations, which could be relevant to the field of computer security (cs.CR) and systems and control (cs.SI).
